One pupil feared dead  There was confusion at Akungba Akoko in Akoko South West Local Government Area of Ondo State as a school bus was gutted by fire this (Thursday) morning. Report had it that a school pupil was killed while 14 others sustained varying degrees of injuries in the incident. According to an eyewitness, the tragedy occurred around 8am with those in the neighborhood jostling to douse the fire. Parents panicked as news of the incident filtered in. Many of them were said to be running helter-skelter in confusion. It was learnt that one of the victims died at his parents’ residence after being rescued from the fire incident. The survivors were said to have been rushed to the state general hospital in Iwaro Oka for treatment. It was reported that the driver of the bus noticed the fire on the way while heading to school after picking up the pupils from their homes. “lt was when people noticed smoke in the sky that they ran towards the area. They later discovered that it was a school bus that was gutted by fire and that the pupils were inside the bus. “They had to immediately break the rear shield of the bus after they discovered that the doors were locked. “We heard that those injured were immediately rushed to the hospital,” an eyewitness (preferred anonymity) said. The Police Public Relations Officer, Ondo State Command, Funmi Odunlami, confirm the incident, saying, “The children are in the hospital but information has it that one of them passed on in his parent’s house.” 